BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Slimy Sallies\, McCormick's Creek State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260524T153000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260524T160000
UID:1300b6eccf20c91b99797e2634fa8d66@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:(Craft) Why are Salamanders so slimy? Drop by the Nature Cente
 r anytime between 3:30 pm-4 pm to learn why slime helps salamanders surviv
 e. Meet our live Tiger Salamander and create your own slime to take home w
 ith Naturalist Kaitlyn! &nbsp\;
LOCATION:McCormick's Creek State Park\, Nature Center\, 250 McCormick's Cr
 eek Park Road\, Spencer\, IN 47460
URL:on.in.gov/mccormickscreek
X-SOURCE:McCormick's Creek State Park
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wolf Cave Hike\, McCormick's Creek State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260525T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260525T123000
UID:cb458bba61a3875aa128334b24372541@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:(Hike) Are you curious what a tornado can do in 30 seconds? Jo
 in Naturalist Kaitlyn to learn about the impact of the tornado to Wolf Cav
 e. This hike is 2.8 miles and will have the option to go through Wolf Cave
 . Please bring a flashlight and wear closed toed shoes. Wolf Cave is wet a
 nd has tight spaces! We will begin this hike at the Nature Center.
LOCATION:McCormick's Creek State Park\, Nature Center\, 250 McCormick's Cr
 eek Park Road\, Spencer\, IN 47460
URL:on.in.gov/mccormickscreek
X-SOURCE:McCormick's Creek State Park
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Fossil Discovery and Geology Hike\, McCormick's Creek State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260525T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260525T153000
UID:16ed84f1225ac10d800d27a73a3d5529@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:(Hike) Take a trip back in time to when Indiana was an ocean f
 loor! Learn about ancient creatures from the skeletons they left behind in
  the limestone. Join DNR Kaitlyn on a rugged hike on the recently reopened
  Trail 3. We will scrabble through rocks in the creek to learn about fossi
 ls older than dinosaurs and how the canyon was formed and altered over geo
 logical history. We begin our 0.8-mile hike in front of the Canyon Inn. &n
 bsp\;
LOCATION:McCormick's Creek State Park\, Canyon Inn\, 250 McCormick's Creek
  Park Road\, Spencer\, IN 47460
URL:on.in.gov/mccormickscreek
X-SOURCE:McCormick's Creek State Park
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Springhouse Salamanders\, McCormick's Creek State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260528T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260528T150000
UID:6cfb5eedb058f9c8b6bb8fa8ee81e305@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:(Hike) Meet Naturalist Jessica at Deer Run Shelter to take a s
 hort hike on Trail 9 to see what salamanders are living in the Springhouse
  . We recommend wearing shoes\, you don&rsquo\;t mind getting wet! &nbsp\;
LOCATION:McCormick's Creek State Park\, Deer Run Shelter\, 250 McCormick's
  Creek Park Road\, Spencer\, IN 47460
URL:on.in.gov/mccormickscreek
X-SOURCE:McCormick's Creek State Park
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Turtle Trot\, McCormick's Creek State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260529T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260529T100000
UID:9eb399f1c1b3ed5f0399e498e07971fe@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:(Live Animals) Eastern Box Turtles will travel up to a mile to
  find a mate. It is imperative turtles have accesses to large amount of la
 nd to wonder around and have fun. Come meet some of our animal ambassadors
  at the Canyon Inn front lawn . &nbsp\;
LOCATION:McCormick's Creek State Park\, Canyon Inn\, 250 McCormick's Creek
  Park Road\, Spencer\, IN 47460
URL:on.in.gov/mccormickscreek
X-SOURCE:McCormick's Creek State Park
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Hiking through History\, McCormick's Creek State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260529T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260529T153000
UID:918c828e83667a5bd4beff873a302214@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:(Hike) Join Naturalist Kaitlyn on a hike to talk about the you
 ng woman who is consider the mother of nature tour guides. Through perseve
 rance and passion\, Lucy change how Indiana learns about nature and encour
 aged countless people to spend time outside. This hike is 1.2 miles and st
 arts from Deer Run Shelter.
LOCATION:McCormick's Creek State Park\, Deer Run Shelter\, 250 McCormick's
  Creek Park Road\, Spencer\, IN 47460
URL:on.in.gov/mccormickscreek
X-SOURCE:McCormick's Creek State Park
END:VEVENT
